history.text: Ever read the novel The Great Gatsby?
Have you watch any of the films including the new one
Yeah. I liked the recent one with Leo.
Definitely! There’s an older movie but the recent one is a lot better
Yeah and the movie does the book justice!

BTW, a professor of literature argued not too long ago that Gatsby's secret was that he was "passing", ie he was a black man passing for a white one. Really. That would be an interesting take for a movie.
Now that you think about it... that’s an excellent theory. Thank you for that
Yeah interesting take. He offers some details as to why, focusing on racial steroetypes during the Jazz Age, iirc. You can google it easily, btw.
This movie was an easy watch. Not sure if critics liked it though, probably because the book sets a high standard.
Cause in the film they sort of romanticize the ghetto where blacks people where almost glamorized. That sort adds to the theory
Yeah the critics gave it like a 50% rating
Gatsby's friend is named Buchanan. I wonder is that is a reference to President James Buchanan and the Dred Scott decision. Just speculation on my part. Not sure if the Prof said this.
I mean Buchanan does hate Gatsby because he is "new money". So it makes sense.
DiCaprio does a good job playing rich guys, which is kinda ironic since he started off in Titanic.
The settings (The Plaza and the North Shore of LI) help make the movie an easy watch, imo.
